This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as sentence embeddings. Additionally, the paper evaluates the robustness of several sentence embedding methods, which is a common research area in cs.CL. 

The paper also involves the use of pre-trained neural sentence encoders, which suggests that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the paper investigates the effects of word substitution errors on sentence embeddings, which is a problem that can be addressed using artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, the paper could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper's focus on textual similarity tasks and the use of word vectors suggest that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which often involves the use of text-based methods for image and video analysis. 

Finally, the paper's use of a simulator to induce ASR-plausible word substitution errors suggests that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SD (Sound).
